<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-11-27T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-11-27T15:00:00-05:00" n="758" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d758">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">138 Emergency Program/368: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Calcutta</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">White</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-27T15:00:00-05:00">November
                                    27, 1939—3 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your 24th.<note n="74" xml:id="d758fn74">Not printed.</note> Passports of
                            American women married to belligerents may not be endorsed for travel
                            into combat area except in cases of imperative necessity such as
                            critical illness or other impelling cause. American women travelling
                            into combat area on foreign passports are liable to penalties set forth
                            in Neutrality Act of 1939.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>